namedLocations.description: Ahmedabad (/ˈəhmədɑːbɑːd/ is the largest city and former capital of the Indian state of Gujarat. It is the administrative headquarters of the Ahmadabad district and the seat of the Gujarat High Court. Ahmedabad's population of 5,633,927 (as per 2011 population census) makes it the fifth-most populous city in India, and the encompassing urban agglomeration population estimated at 6,357,693 is the seventh-most populous in India. Ahmadabad is located on the banks of the Sabarmati River, 30 km (19 mi) from the state capital Gandhinagar, which is its twin city.

transcript.text: Hello everyone and welcome back to our order management tutorial series.
In today's video, we will walk you through the steps to initiate a refund for a cancelled order in the On Print Shop platform.
There can be times when you might need to manage order cancellations for customers to return purchased items and refund the payment.
Refunding promptly and professionally shows your commitment to your customers and encourages them to order again in the future.
In on Print Shop, the admin can decide to allow for order cancellations based on the order status or order product status.
Let's first understand the order cancellation process from the order status section.
When you allow order cancellations for some statuses, the order being in that status will give an option to customers to cancel their orders.
For example, 1 customer has ordered a business card which is in a pending state.
As per the configuration, you have allowed cancellations.
So from their My Orders section, when they see the order details, they will have a request for cancellation button at the top of the page.
Once they click on that button, the system will ask for the reason for the cancellation.
The customers can select the appropriate reason and then click on submit.
The admin will receive the notification of the request, and from the order listing page, the admin can verify that the order is in cancellation request status.
After viewing the details, the admin can opt to reject the request if the order is already in the printing or finishing stage, or they can refund the payment.
Let's see how you can refund the payment if you have received any cancellation request from your customer.
Navigate to the admin panel from the Order section and click on List Orders.
Locate the order and from the Actions drop down, click on the View Update Order.
On the View Update Order page, you will find the Refund button.
You can choose to refund for the entire order or individual products ordered.
Click on the refund button to proceed.
In the popup, you can see the reason for the cancellation request and the option to reject the request.
If you accept the cancellation, then proceed with the refund, you have three ways to refund the payment.
If there was no payment made, you can choose Order cancel only or if you want to process the refund amount manually or if you want to refund the payment in the form of a coupon.

When you are just canceling the order, you need to select the next status of the order, add your remarks, choose if you want to restock the product quantity, choose to reset the coupon or reward points if the customer has used them during checkout.
If you want to notify your customer about this action, then keep the Notify checkbox ticked and save.
When you choose to perform the manual refund, you need to specify if you are refunding a full payment or part of the payment.
Depending on the scenario, verify the prefilled details or enter the subtotal amount, shipping charges, tax and processing fees that you want to refund.
Define the other details and then save.
While going with the refund via Coupon refund type, you get options the same as manual refund.
The only difference is that in this method, a coupon code will be generated for the payment amount and it can be availed in the next order.
The coupon code will be displayed in the View History tab in the admin panel and on the front end.
The customers will also be able to see the code in the order history.
The coupon details will also be displayed on the Coupon Discount listing page.
You can manage the notification emails for cancelled and refunded orders from the Order Status e-mail tab under the e-mail Notifications section.
And there you have it.
Providing A seamless cancellation and refund process can enhance the overall customer experience and build trust in your online print shop.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
